pageContext.claim: “But if Biden wins, your borders are gone, which means your healthcare is gone, the middle class is gone, your safety is gone, your country is gone. That's what's going to happen and don't think it can't happen. [Audience Boos] Take a look at Venezuela. This could be -- same ideology is what they're talking about. This could be a Venezuela but much, much, much bigger. It could happen, it could happen.”
pageContext.analysis: This is a nonsense fear tactic. Trump's claim originates with the Democrats who have embraced some socialist policies. While Venezuela is governed by socialist leaders, its status as an increasingly failed state follows years of dictatorship and economic mismanagement, not simply a few socialist policies.
